iracy count and one forgerycount.   If convicted, Herbst would face up to 31 years in prison and$70,000 in fines. Rich would face 40 years in prison and up to$90,000 in fines.   Herbst told lottery officials he had been using the ticket as abookmark.</TEXT></DOC>